name: Utopia
description:
Text reads: 
"And then all wars ended. Arms of every kind were outlawed and the masses gladly contributed them to giant foundries in which they were melted down and the metal poured back into the earth. The Pentagon was turned on its side and painted purple, yellow and green. All boundaries were dissolved. The slaughter of animals was forbidden.... World health was restored. An abundance of organic vegetables, fruits and grains was growing along the discarded highways. National flags were sewn together into brightly colored circus tents under which politicians were allowed to perform harmless theatrical games. The concept of work was forgotten."

Five color, Five pull,  Artists Silk Screen print. Limited edition, Signed and Numbered, 18 x 24 inches, on white 80lb vellum stock. Shipped rolled, in a crush proof tube. Contact me for shipping rates outside the US.
